{"id":14881039,"mediaExerciseId":"1658ce70-cabd-4e94-ac0e-2f1ff2eef4fd","exerciseName":"5","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612312,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":232,"solutions":[{"id":5968740,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks **to advise the company whether to include an option in bonds and whether it should be a call or put option**.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/1c031b6d9f21ae9cb13d6300c6be006a/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/1c031b6d9f21ae9cb13d6300c6be006a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**The call option** on the security allows the issuer to repurchase the security if the market interest rate decreases. **It means the issuer can offer the same bond again, but the coupon rate will be lower. If the company has a covenant with a debtholder by using this option, the company can cancel this agreement.** *Those are the advantages of this option*.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/981f756a94b58349910bf5f3ab0e54f0/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/981f756a94b58349910bf5f3ab0e54f0/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"A protective covenant is one of the elements of indenture or other debt agreements. A protective covenant is a limitation that does not allow the debtor to take risky activities and put the company in a dangerous position. This limitation protects the lender and helps him receive the money back.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/a88c929a68f097366d9143ecb0949afa/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/a88c929a68f097366d9143ecb0949afa/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**Because the investors are taking the risk of reinvestment, the issuer has to offer a higher coupon payment to be attractive for the investors.** *That is the disadvantage for the company.*","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/dd18a0ca62bf5a7220b54d58d406cbbb/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/dd18a0ca62bf5a7220b54d58d406cbbb/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**The put option** is the opposite. The bondholder can press the issuer and force him to pay the principal amount of the security. The holder can use this option when he sees that the security's price is falling on the market. Because if the bondholder uses this option, the company will be in a worse position, the cost of this bond is lower. The coupon payment will be lower.\n\n**So, the disadvantage of this option for the company will be to buy the security when its price falls. The advantage is low coupon payment.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":256,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/4c43d677233a1883182ee0ff06356b49/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/e8203957012d8418246696060176ad61/4c43d677233a1883182ee0ff06356b49/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"c5a4decd-f4ae-4853-9d2d-e87586b8cc28","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881040,"exerciseName":"6","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c7615607-95a6-4677-8198-4a41a1997c3a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-6-c7615607-95a6-4677-8198-4a41a1997c3a"},{"id":14881041,"exerciseName":"7","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"3581a35f-1349-4d66-ab74-0351b6bf83e0","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-7-3581a35f-1349-4d66-ab74-0351b6bf83e0"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881038,"exerciseName":"4","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5eda5edc-2e4f-412a-8c75-a7a132abfa76","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-4-5eda5edc-2e4f-412a-8c75-a7a132abfa76"},{"id":14881037,"exerciseName":"3","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"60df86ae-a6ef-48cf-a675-22c8ecea1464","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-3-60df86ae-a6ef-48cf-a675-22c8ecea1464"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-critical-thinking-questions-5-1658ce70-cabd-4e94-ac0e-2f1ff2eef4fd"}